were based on
total popular vote, I would have
campaigned

01:37.831 --> 01:43.103 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
in New York, Florida and
California and won
even bigger and more easily."

01:43.136 --> 01:48.075 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
President Obama urged world
leaders today
to heed the lessons of Donald
Trump's election.

01:48.108 --> 01:51.244 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The president spoke in Athens
after talks
with Greek Prime Minister Alexis
Tsipras.

01:51.278 --> 01:56.383 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He said voters are scared their
children will
be less well-off, and he issued
a warning.

01:56.416 --> 02:01.254 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BARACK OBAMA, President of the
United States:
We are going to have to guard
against a rise

02:01.288 --> 02:11.298 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in a crude sort of nationalism,
or ethnic
identity, or tribalism that is
built around

02:11.331 --> 02:13.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
an us and a them.

02:13.200 --> 02:16.770 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: The president
also defended
his own economic record, saying
the country's

02:16.803 --> 02:19.106 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
indisputably better off.

02:19.139 --> 02:23.777 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
France and the U.N. today
stepped up appeals
to president-elect Trump not to
quit a global

02:23.810 --> 02:25.946 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
accord on climate change.

02:25.979 --> 02:30.150 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
French President Francois
Hollande said dropping
out of the Paris agreement would
be disastrous

02:30.183 --> 02:31.885 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
for future generations.

02:31.918 --> 02:38.191 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
U.N. Secretary Ban Ki-Moon
agreed, but said
he's sure the incoming president
will make

02:38.225 --> 02:40.761 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
a good and wise decision.

02:40.794 --> 02:44.998 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
House Speaker Paul Ryan has won
the unanimous
support of his fellow
Republicans to stay

02:45.032 --> 02:46.700 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
on the job.

02:46.733 --> 02:50.570 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Their vote today clears the way
for the full
House to make it official come
January.

02:50.604 --> 02:54.441 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Before today's vote, Ryan said
he's ready
and eager, with Republicans
controlling both

02:54.474 --> 02:56.910 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Congress and the White House
starting next
year.

02:56.943 --> 02:58.879 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

02:58.912 --> 03:02.516 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAUL RYAN (R-WI), Speaker of the
House: Welcome
to the dawn of a new unified
Republican government.

03:02.549 --> 03:05.585 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It feels really good to say
that, actually.

03:05.619 --> 03:09.756 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This will be a government
focused on turning
president-elect Trump's victory
into real

03:09.790 --> 03:11.992 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
progress for the American
people.

03:12.025 --> 03:14.761 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Our team is very excited and we
cannot wait
to get to work.

03:14.795 --> 03:19.266 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Meanwhile,
Democrats delayed
their leadership contest for
another two weeks,

03:19.299 --> 03:22.035 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
amid dissatisfaction over the
election results.

03:22.069 --> 03:26.239 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's unclear if Minority Leader
Nancy Pelosi
will face a serious challenge,
but more than

03:26.273 --> 03:29.976 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
two dozen Democrats asked to
delay the vote.

03:30.010 --> 03:34.114 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In Syria, a three-week break in
airstrikes
on Aleppo is over.

03:34.147 --> 03:39.252 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Syrian planes blasted rebels in
the city today,
and Russia launched a new air
offensive elsewhere.

03:39.286 --> 03:45.225 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Russian jets from an aircraft
carrier and
long-range missiles hit targets
in two provinces.

03:45.258 --> 03:49.062 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Moscow says they targeted
Islamic State militants
and others.

03:49.096 --> 03:54.768 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The State Department is playing
down findings
that American troops and the CIA
may be guilty

03:54.801 --> 03:56.870 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
of war crimes in Afghanistan.

03:56.903 --> 03:59.539 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The report comes from the
International Criminal
Court.

03:59.573 --> 04:04.010 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In it, the chief prosecutor says
the detainees
were subject to torture, cruel
treatment,

04:04.044 --> 04:08.682 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and outrages upon personal
dignity between
2003 and 2014.

04:08.715 --> 04:15.288 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The U.S. is not part of the
court, but any
American who's indicted could
still face prosecution.

04:15.322 --> 04:20.527 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Police in Germany carried out
raids today
on nearly 200 apartments,
offices and mosques

04:20.560 --> 04:23.296 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
tied to a newly banned Islamist
group.

04:23.330 --> 04:27.234 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It allegedly recruited youths to
fight in
Iraq and Syria.

04:27.267 --> 04:31.805 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Officers collected troves of
documents, hard
drives and weapons as evidence.

04:31.838 --> 04:35.842 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The raids took place in more
than 60 cities.

04:35.876 --> 04:40.914 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There's word that Chinese
software in some
Android phones automatically
sends data back

04:40.947 --> 04:42.782 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to a server in China.

04:42.816 --> 04:48.288 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The New York Times reports the
software monitors
locations, call logs and text
messages.

04:48.321 --> 04:52.959 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
International customers and
users of disposable
or prepaid phones are most
affected.

04:52.993 --> 04:57.664 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The data collection could be for
advertising
usage or intelligence.

04:57.697 --> 05:02.769 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And on Wall Street, energy
stocks led the
market higher as oil prices
surged 6 percent,

05:02.802 --> 05:05.705 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
amid talk that OPEC will cut
output.

05:05.739 --> 05:09.042 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Dow Jones industrial average
gained 54
points to close at 18923.

05:09.075 --> 05:14.581 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Nasdaq rose 57 points, and
the S&amp;P 500
added 16.

05:14.614 --> 05:18.885 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Still to come on the "NewsHour":
what the
president-elect's staff picks
tell us about

05:18.919 --> 05:24.491 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
his policies; recent tensions in
race relations
and what they may portend for
the future;

05:24.524 --> 05:30.230 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a psychotherapist's struggle
with his own
trauma one year after the Paris
attacks; and

05:30.263 --> 05:41.875 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
much more.

05:41.908 --> 05:46.846 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Now we turn to president-elect
Trump's transition
to the White House and how his
team is tackling

05:46.880 --> 05:49.382 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the handover of executive reins.

05:49.416 --> 05:51.651 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
