Isenstadt
of Politico.

05:51.685 --> 05:53.420 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, Alex, you're reporting on
this every today.

05:53.453 --> 05:55.088 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Where do things stand right now?

05:55.121 --> 05:58.358 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ALEX ISENSTADT, Politico: Well,
look, it's
a transition that's very much in
flux.

05:58.391 --> 06:04.297 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And you're starting to see a
pattern here
of a Donald Trump sort of
overseeing a process

06:04.331 --> 06:06.766 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
that very much was sort of like
his campaign.

06:06.800 --> 06:08.568 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
There was a little bit of chaos
involved.

06:08.602 --> 06:12.639 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You're sort of starting to see
some of that
chaos seep into the transition a
little bit.

06:12.672 --> 06:16.943 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And perhaps this is a little --
perhaps this
provides an indication of what
Donald Trump's

06:16.977 --> 06:19.913 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
management and leadership style
is going to
be like once he gets to the
White House.

06:19.946 --> 06:22.115 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: And Chris
Christie was demoted
last week.

06:22.148 --> 06:23.583 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Mike Pence replaced him.

06:23.617 --> 06:26.820 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And he's overarching the kind of
lead on this.

06:26.853 --> 06:28.655 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But there's been some internal
strife.

06:28.688 --> 06:30.490 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We hear Mike Rogers stepped
down.

06:30.523 --> 06:32.325 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
What was behind that?

06:32.359 --> 06:36.196 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ALEX ISENSTADT: Well, look, Mike
Rogers, former
congressman from Michigan, used
to head the

06:36.229 --> 06:41.067 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
