28:15.694 --> 28:17.563 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We need to reach out to Trump
supporters.

28:17.596 --> 28:23.702 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, you know, we call on our
government officials
to visit mosques, visit temples,
so that we

28:23.735 --> 28:26.305 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
can work together and unite and
heal, rather
than divide.

28:26.338 --> 28:30.008 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: All right,
Rizwan Jaka,
Mark Potok from the Southern
Poverty Law Center,

28:30.042 --> 28:31.443 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Eddie Glaude from Princeton,
thank you all.

28:31.476 --> 28:32.878 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
RIZWAN JAKA: Thank you.

28:32.911 --> 28:34.680 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
EDDIE GLAUDE: Thank you.

28:34.713 --> 28:38.817 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Tonight, PBS
presents the
first part of a documentary
miniseries from

28:38.850 --> 28:45.457 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Harvard University Professor
Henry Louis Gates:
"Black America Since MLK: And
Still I Rise."

28:45.490 --> 28:49.962 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This clip from tonight's episode
examines
why the phrase "I'm black and I
am proud"

28:49.995 --> 28:52.764 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
was a radical idea in 1968.

28:52.798 --> 28:59.871 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NARRATOR: Even soul brother
number one, the
immensely popular James Brown,
abandoned his

28:59.905 --> 29:05.410 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
signature patent leather
processed hairstyle
for a natural kinky-headed afro.

29:05.444 --> 29:06.411 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
MAN: Hello.

29:06.445 --> 29:07.913 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
This is Don River (ph).

29:07.946 --> 29:09.314 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
You're on "Black Dignity."

29:09.348 --> 29:11.116 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MAN: Yes, what's happening,
James?

29:11.149 --> 29:12.651 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MD-BO / I just wanted to ask you
one question.

29:12.684 --> 29:14.519 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I would like to know why you got
your process
cut.

29:14.553 --> 29:16.455 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JAMES BROWN, Musician: Well,
this is a black
move.

29:16.488 --> 29:20.225 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And regardless of what you were
thinking,
we have all got to think one
way.

29:20.258 --> 29:21.593 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And if we look alike, we can
think alike.

29:21.627 --> 29:24.596 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MAN: The way I see it, it's what
really in
your mind that counts.

29:24.630 --> 29:29.301 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JAMES BROWN: Well, the mind
counts, but, see,
we all don't have a good image.

29:29.334 --> 29:31.269 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And image is, like, black.

29:31.303 --> 29:33.572 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
See, we have never fought
together.

29:33.605 --> 29:36.308 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In Africa, a man can do what he
want to do
because he know who he is.

29:36.341 --> 29:37.542 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Over here, you don't know.

29:37.576 --> 29:39.645 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, first, we have got to get
our image, an
identity.

29:39.678 --> 29:44.516 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
NARRATOR: And Brown didn't just
change his
look.

29:44.549 --> 29:50.222 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He also recorded a song that
would become
a black power anthem.

29:50.255 --> 30:00.298 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WOMAN: When we think about, "Say
it loud,
I'm black and I'm proud," we
have got to remember

30:00.298 --> 30:06.538 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WOMAN: When we think about, "Say
it loud,
I'm black and I'm proud," we
have got to remember

30:06.571 --> 30:16.648 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
what a thinker Brown was about
how to deal
in segregated, racist, apartheid
America.

30:16.682 --> 30:20.952 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
James Brown understood from the
experience
he had as a child.

30:20.986 --> 30:25.457 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Dark-skinned black people are
especially hated
in this culture.

30:25.490 --> 30:33.565 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They are seen as the true black
people worth
hating.

30:33.598 --> 30:37.302 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JAMES PETERSON, Lehigh
University: James Brown's
impact on the cultural life of
people my age

30:37.335 --> 30:39.171 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
is profound.

30:39.204 --> 30:43.942 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There's a way in which the music
that he makes,
I don't know if unmitigated
blackness is the

30:43.975 --> 30:47.746 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
right way to frame it, but he's
just black.

30:47.779 --> 30:50.282 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
You know what I'm saying?

30:50.315 --> 30:53.885 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Like, unashamed, direct,
forthright, powerful,
in-your-face black.

30:53.919 --> 31:04.696 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: "Black America
Since MLK:
And Still I Rise" tonight on
