31:04.730 --> 31:16.241 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
8:00 Eastern, 7:00 Central.

31:16.274 --> 31:18.043 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Stay with us.

31:18.076 --> 31:22.114 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Coming up on the "NewsHour": a
couple's love
that broke through all
boundaries; and an

31:22.147 --> 31:26.952 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
outpouring of tributes to our
colleague Gwen
Ifill.

31:26.985 --> 31:31.223 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
France has been commemorating
the first anniversary
of the Paris attacks, where ISIS
militants

31:31.256 --> 31:35.393 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
killed 130 people and wounded
nearly 400.

31:35.427 --> 31:40.699 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The attack on Friday the 13th
last year was
the worst on French soil since
the Second

31:40.732 --> 31:41.967 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
World War.

31:42.000 --> 31:45.904 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, how are the survivors coping
with the
trauma one year on?

31:45.937 --> 31:50.509 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Last year, we talked to Mark
Colclough, a
British-Danish psychotherapist
who witnessed

31:50.542 --> 31:52.477 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the killings at a cafe.

31:52.511 --> 31:56.448 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Special correspondent Malcolm
Brabant has
been back to see him at home.

31:56.481 --> 32:02.888 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: We're driving
to Funen, Denmark's
central island, where Mark
Colclough now resides.

32:02.921 --> 32:07.559 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's 100 miles from his previous
home in the
capital, Copenhagen.

32:07.592 --> 32:12.297 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In the search for peace of mind,
he's found
it necessary to immerse himself
in the tranquility

32:12.330 --> 32:13.799 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of nature.

32:13.832 --> 32:16.835 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARK COLCLOUGH, Psychotherapist:
Paris has
changed us on a profound level.

32:16.868 --> 32:19.671 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's so profound, that we can't
quite touch
it yet.

32:19.704 --> 32:24.075 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Within that change for me the
last year, I
have noticed how much I need to
get away from

32:24.109 --> 32:29.548 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the city and get away from
congregations of
people and sudden movement, and
this kind

32:29.581 --> 32:35.353 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of -- you know, the head tick
buzz of -- Copenhagen's
not a busy city, by any means,
compared to

32:35.387 --> 32:38.723 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Paris, but it's a lot busier
than this.

32:38.757 --> 32:42.561 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I have really felt the need
to have some
space, some peace and quiet,
where I can just

32:42.594 --> 32:44.963 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
be myself and I can predict
what's happening.

32:44.996 --> 32:46.998 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm an ordinary guy.

32:47.032 --> 32:50.902 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I was walking down the
street in Paris
on an ordinary evening in
November, and I

32:50.936 --> 32:56.575 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
saw absolutely extraordinary
events, have
changed my view on myself, have
changed my

32:56.608 --> 32:58.310 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
view on humanity entirely.

32:58.343 --> 32:59.911 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: How have you
been doing?

32:59.945 --> 33:01.880 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MARK COLCLOUGH: It's been a long
journey.

33:01.913 --> 33:05.684 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I can hardly believe it's been
almost a year
already.

33:05.717 --> 33:11.923 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I looked through the interview
that we did
in November last year, when we
met.

33:11.957 --> 33:17.562 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I can see then that I
assumed, two, three
weeks of this, I will be fine,
back to work

33:17.596 --> 33:19.297 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
as usual.

33:19.331 --> 33:22.234 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: But Colclough
didn't return
to work as a psychotherapist for
a couple

33:22.267 --> 33:23.235 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of months.

33:23.268 --> 33:26.171 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And then he frequently required
time off.

33:26.204 --> 33:27.939 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Do you think you're going to be
permanently
damaged?

33:27.973 --> 33:30.342 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARK COLCLOUGH: Oh, no, no, I
don't think
that at all.

33:30.375 --> 33:34.346 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: Is that because
you personally
and professionally have the
tools that enable

33:34.379 --> 33:35.347 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
you to deal with this?

33:35.380 --> 33:36.448 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
MARK COLCLOUGH: Yes, I think.

33:36.481 --> 33:39.484 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I have been in and out of
therapy since I
was 19.

33:39.517 --> 33:42.754 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's always been in my interest,
has been
psychotherapy and psychology.

33:42.787 --> 33:46.758 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So I'm aware that I have tools,
and I have
a quite robust sense of self.

33:46.791 --> 33:50.495 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And now it's a year later, and I
have had
a really good year.

33:50.528 --> 33:55.367 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The first couple of months were
very difficult,and
then the summer gradually got
better and better.

33:55.400 --> 33:58.370 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And then the last couple of
weeks, I have
seen a bit of a downturn again.

33:58.403 --> 34:02.540 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: Returning to
Paris for the
anniversary has affected his
state of mind.

34:02.574 --> 34:04.910 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARK COLCLOUGH: I have been back
in Paris
twice.

34:04.943 --> 34:09.447 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And returning to the scene of
the shootings
has been incredibly full of
anxiety before

34:09.481 --> 34:14.552 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
going, but actually being there
has been incredibly
healing.

34:14.586 --> 34:21.826 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: Mark Colclough
says that
one of the reasons why he's
suffered a psychological

34:21.860 --> 34:27.399 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
set setback this year is due to
a decision
by the French authority
responsible for distributing

34:27.432 --> 34:30.035 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
compensation for victims of
terrorism.

34:30.068 --> 34:34.139 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They have turned down his
application because
they say he was outside on the
street as a

34:34.172 --> 34:37.676 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
witness and wasn't inside the
cafe when the
shooting took place.

34:37.709 --> 34:42.547 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Now, he's disputing this
decision, saying
that he has suffered
post-traumatic stress

34:42.580 --> 34:47.285 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
disorder for the past year, and,
as a result,
he has had to cut back on work
by 60 percent.

34:47.319 --> 34:50.355 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MARK COLCLOUGH: I'm not looking
for the money.

34:50.388 --> 34:51.356 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Even the money feels weird.

34:51.389 --> 34:53.325 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It feels like bloody money
somehow.

34:53.358 --> 34:58.430 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But I took it as if, as an
authority, they're
saying that the feelings I do
have, the flashbacks

34:58.463 --> 35:04.169 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I do have, the nightmares I
still have, that
I'm somehow either not entitled
or less entitled

35:04.202 --> 35:05.170 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to them somehow.

35:05.203 --> 35:06.871 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: Have you become
more altruistic?

35:06.905 --> 35:09.474 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Have you become less selfish,
less materialistic?

35:09.507 --> 35:13.578 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARK COLCLOUGH: I have downsized
my life in
many ways.

35:13.611 --> 35:17.949 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And my friends and my close --
my close friends
and family have said to me,
pretty much across

35:17.983 --> 35:22.420 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the board, that even though what
I have gone
through in Paris was horrific,
it's changed

35:22.454 --> 35:29.027 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
me, has made me more human, more
vulnerable,
more available to them.

35:29.060 --> 35:32.397 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And I find myself tearing up
easily.

35:32.430 --> 35:38.536 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I find myself being more moved
by something
more easily, the human gesture,
how much we

35:38.570 --> 35:41.172 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
can touch each other by doing
something very
simple for each other.

35:41.206 --> 35:45.010 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: Last year,
Colclough was
quite certain that he wouldn't
suffer from

35:45.043 --> 35:49.347 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
survivor's guilt, and would
replace it with
what he called survivor's
obligation.

35:49.381 --> 35:54.085 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARK COLCLOUGH: I think the
obligation to
live, to live fully and to give
something

35:54.119 --> 35:56.755 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
back to the people that I meet
in my life.

35:56.788 --> 36:02.827 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I saw four people's lives
extinguished very,
very quickly right in front of
me.

36:02.861 --> 36:08.933 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that obligation is to give
something back
to the people I meet in the
course of my life,

36:08.967 --> 36:10.935 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
not just professionally, but
also personally.

36:10.969 --> 36:15.407 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: But his desire
to control
his thoughts and suppress his
subconscious

36:15.440 --> 36:17.175 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
have failed.

36:17.208 --> 36:20.412 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARK COLCLOUGH: The hardest
feeling over the
last year has been guilt, guilty
about not

36:20.445 --> 36:26.418 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
having done more and guilty
about not having
-- I mean, I still have dreams
about me intervening

36:26.451 --> 36:30.455 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
with the gunman and trying to
attack him,
which is -- it was what I was
planning to

36:30.488 --> 36:32.257 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
do.

36:32.290 --> 36:35.093 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I knew that he would be -- or I
assumed he
would be deaf and blinded
somewhat by using

36:35.126 --> 36:37.629 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a high-powered assault rifle
inside a small
cafe.

36:37.662 --> 36:40.165 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I was hoping to attack him
on the way
out.

36:40.198 --> 36:44.002 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And then I decided not to when I
saw he had
two exits from the cafe.

36:44.035 --> 36:45.937 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
So, then I ran.

36:45.970 --> 36:49.107 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But having seen all these
things, and then
the French authorities saying,
well, because

36:49.140 --> 36:55.180 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
you stood on a road, we don't
quite recognize
you as a witness of terrorism,
it's very weird.

36:55.213 --> 36:59.617 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: If you, as a
professional,
are struggling as you are, how
do you think

36:59.651 --> 37:05.623 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
other people are, especially
those, for example,
who weren't just witnesses, but
who were survivors

37:05.657 --> 37:09.928 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in places like the Bataclan,
where there were
bullets flying around their
head?

37:09.961 --> 37:15.033 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARK COLCLOUGH: Yes, and those
shot, not killed,
but wounded and dealing with the
physical

37:15.066 --> 37:16.468 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
aftermath of being shot.

37:16.501 --> 37:20.038 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The path of healing is a very
individual one.

37:20.071 --> 37:25.176 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Many witnesses have formed
informal bonds
and informal friendships that
are strong as

37:25.210 --> 37:27.745 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
concrete.

37:27.779 --> 37:30.682 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I feel that too with the two
witnesses
I'm in touch with.

37:30.715 --> 37:38.123 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Our paths have crossed in a day
that was full
of -- a night that was full of
hatred and

37:38.156 --> 37:40.758 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
carnage, blood and violence.

37:40.792 --> 37:44.395 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And, through that, some very
deep, intimate
friendships have been cast.

37:44.429 --> 37:46.965 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And I don't think they will ever
break.

37:46.998 --> 37:51.736 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: Since the
attacks, fears
of Islamic terrorism have
slammed shut Europe's

37:51.769 --> 37:54.973 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
once open borders and the
continent has lurched
to the right.

37:55.006 --> 38:01.212 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARK COLCLOUGH: It saddens me
entirely that
we think that stricter borders
and shut borders

38:01.246 --> 38:05.617 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and Brexit and other events that
have happened
in Europe will somehow protect
nations like

38:05.650 --> 38:06.618 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
this.

38:06.651 --> 38:11.122 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
It doesn't work.

38:11.156 --> 38:18.029 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
